 ## Teardown
 
-`ClaudeLauncher` kills the tmux session in an `ensure` block, removes the
-per-task `.claude/settings.json`, deletes stale `.done`, and runs a narrow
-`pkill -f` sweep scoped to the task folder's `--add-dir` argument.
-The sweep is defensive; normal cleanup is tmux session termination.
+`ClaudeLauncher` asks Claude to `/quit`, kills the tmux session in an `ensure`
+backstop, restores any project-owned `.claude/settings.json`, removes Hive's
+duplicate scratch settings, and deletes `.done`, `result.json`,
+`claude-exit-status`, and their temporary siblings. It then runs a narrow
+`pgrep` sweep and terminates matched Claude PIDs individually while explicitly
+skipping tmux server processes. The sweep is defensive; normal cleanup is the
+graceful wrapper/session exit.
 
