+### Audit and recover the June 29 Claude tmux review failures
+
+The legacy runs below predate the wrapper exit sidecar, pass-start HEAD, and
+strict `fix-result-NN.json` evidence. Hive therefore cannot safely re-evaluate
+or clear them automatically. Before clearing anything, retain the original
+marker and `events.jsonl`, record who performed the audit, and inspect the PR,
+worktree status and HEAD, current-pass reviewer/escalation artifacts, missing
+output/error artifacts, and every unanswered escalation. For task 288, the
+daemon-global health-gate answer was “OK for v1”; still verify that no other
+unresolved escalation or missing-output marker remains.
+
+After that audit, use these exact commands (add `--project <name>` only when
+the local registry needs disambiguation):
+
+```sh
+# Task 58 / PR #622
+hive markers clear add-local-hive-web-install-260629-f4ca --name REVIEW_ERROR
+hive run add-local-hive-web-install-260629-f4ca
+
+# Task 287 / PR #623
+hive markers clear fix-claude-tmux-ready-detector-260629-50cc --name REVIEW_ERROR
+hive run fix-claude-tmux-ready-detector-260629-50cc
+
+# Task 288 / PR #624
+hive markers clear make-the-hive-daemon-automatically-260629-223d --name REVIEW_ERROR
+hive run make-the-hive-daemon-automatically-260629-223d
+```
+
+Never place unconditional `REVIEW_ERROR` clearing in install, migration, or
+startup automation. On an affected pre-fix release, keep `claude.mode:
+headless` until the fixed release is installed and verified; recovery does not
+re-enable tmux.
