 Plan / worktree.yml / task.md are SHA-256 protected around the fix spawn; tampering → `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_tampered`. The fix protected set also includes the current pass's escalations/errors/fix-success/fix-guardrail files plus `reviews/suppressed.md`, so a fix agent cannot clear or flip the no-fix suppression list. If the fix agent exits with raw provider-limit `limit_text`, or a legacy AgentLimit wire-format error message, the runner writes `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=limits_reached retry_after=<iso8601>` through the same `mark_review_phase_failure` helper used by triage; ordinary fix-agent errors still write `reason=fix_failed`.
 
+The fix prompt must write `reviews/fix-result-NN.json` with the exact keys
+`task_slug`, `pass`, `outcome`, `resolved_findings`, and `resolution`. Hive
+removes stale copies before every spawn and binds the result to the current
+task/pass and accepted-finding count. `changed` requires a clean worktree and
+an advanced HEAD after the scoped/sign-policy-aware auto-commit path;
+`no_change` requires clean Git state, an unchanged HEAD, and explicit prose
+that no code changes were needed or all accepted findings were already
+resolved. Current-pass reviewer and escalation artifacts must remain readable
+and unchanged, `errors-NN.md` must be absent, and no unresolved escalation may
+remain.
+
+Under `claude.mode: tmux`, this evidence is also the stage verifier for the
+shared missing-Stop-signal protocol. The launcher accepts it only after a
+finished readable pane, bounded `/quit`, and wrapper-recorded Claude exit `0`.
+Acceptance emits one WARN `claude_completion_fallback` event containing the
+session/PID, expected sentinel, checked artifacts, task/pass, and before/after
+HEAD or explicit no-change evidence. Event-write failure is fail-closed. A
+rejected candidate preserves `REVIEW_ERROR phase=fix reason=fix_failed` and the
+legacy `claude stop hook did not signal completion` diagnostic.
